    "body" : "@E.Ar, performance can be different only if String is appended inside loop. Explicitly declaring StringBuilder before loop is a must to have good results, omitting this will result in creating StringBuilders objects on every iteration. But without loops concating strings is translated to StringBuilders by default (in byte code), from java 1.5, so there&#39;s not need to replace <code>+</code> with <code>StringBuilders.append(string)</code> in simple cases."
  } ],
